WEBVTT

00:02.635 --> 00:03.969
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.037 --> 00:05.705
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.772 --> 00:07.240
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.307 --> 00:08.641
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:08.708 --> 00:10.543
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:10.610 --> 00:13.980
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:14.047 --> 00:15.048
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:15.115 --> 00:16.483
<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.549 --> 00:17.650
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:17.717 --> 00:19.386
<i>♪ Is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:19.452 --> 00:21.421
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.488 --> 00:22.922
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:22.989 --> 00:24.924
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.991 --> 00:28.061
<i>- ♪ Loud Loud Loud ♪</i>

00:28.128 --> 00:29.396
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:29.462 --> 00:30.597
{\an8}- Poo-poo.

00:34.834 --> 00:37.771
{\an8}<i>[rock music]</i>

00:37.837 --> 00:45.445
{\an8}<i>♪</i> ♪

00:45.512 --> 00:47.947
<i>- ♪ Yeah! ♪</i>

00:48.014 --> 00:50.049
♪ Take my advice
and don't be a mooch ♪

00:50.116 --> 00:53.420
♪ Grab life by the lips
and give it a smooch <i> ♪</i>

00:53.486 --> 00:54.854
♪ Whoo <i> ♪</i>

00:54.921 --> 00:56.089
<i>♪ Give it a smooch ♪</i>

00:56.156 --> 00:59.359
{\an1}- Clyde,
Smooch is the coolest band ever.

00:59.426 --> 01:00.393
- Copy that.

01:00.460 --> 01:01.594
I'd totally give life a smooch

01:01.661 --> 01:04.697
{\an3}if I wasn't
saving my lips for Lori.

01:04.763 --> 01:07.434
- Clyde and I are going to see
Smooch tonight,

01:07.500 --> 01:09.135
and not to make
a big deal of it,

01:09.202 --> 01:11.638
but it's our first concert.

01:11.704 --> 01:15.442
Okay, Clyde, meet you at the
ticket line in T-minus one hour.

01:15.508 --> 01:18.445
- Okay, that'll give me time
to work on my dance moves.

01:18.511 --> 01:21.281
[grunts]
Oh!

01:21.347 --> 01:23.683
{\an3}- Aah!

01:23.750 --> 01:25.385
- Simmer down and listen up.

01:25.452 --> 01:28.288
- We overheard your conversation
and we're here to warn you.

01:28.354 --> 01:29.722
- Do not let Luna know

01:29.789 --> 01:31.324
{\an3}that you're going
to your first concert.

01:31.391 --> 01:33.626
She'll insist on going with you.

01:33.693 --> 01:35.028
- What?
Why?

01:35.094 --> 01:36.463
{\an3}- I don't know,
'cause she's nuts?

01:36.529 --> 01:38.798
{\an3}But she's done it
to all of us.

01:38.865 --> 01:40.467
- Yeah, and when she goes,

01:40.533 --> 01:44.537
{\an1}she gets way too excited
and literally ruins everything.

01:44.604 --> 01:47.240
There was my first
Boyz Will Be Boyz concert.

01:47.307 --> 01:49.742
- ♪ Ooh, girl, if I could ♪

01:49.809 --> 01:51.544
♪ Ooh, girl, give you the ♪

01:51.611 --> 01:53.746
- [sobbing]

01:53.813 --> 01:56.716
I love you!

01:56.783 --> 01:58.585
- Come on, people.

01:58.651 --> 02:01.988
Where's your energy?

02:02.055 --> 02:04.591
[electricity crackles]

02:04.657 --> 02:05.892
- ♪ Ooh, girl ♪

02:05.959 --> 02:09.095
- And our first
Blarney the Dinosaur concert.

02:09.162 --> 02:10.930
- ♪ Moo goes the cow ♪

02:10.997 --> 02:12.365
♪ Oink goes the pig ♪

02:12.432 --> 02:15.435
♪ Watch me do me Irish jig ♪

02:15.502 --> 02:18.771
- Come on, guys.
Crowd surf!

02:21.140 --> 02:23.009
- And my first opera.

02:23.076 --> 02:26.212
- [singing in foreign language]

02:28.748 --> 02:29.949
- Check it, Lis!

02:30.016 --> 02:31.951
Stage dive!

02:32.018 --> 02:34.153
- [screams]
[horns squeal]

02:34.220 --> 02:35.655
{\an3}- Oh, man.

02:35.722 --> 02:37.223
{\an3}I can't let Luna
find out about Smooch.

02:37.290 --> 02:38.525
- Don't worry.

02:38.591 --> 02:40.493
{\an1}We can get you out
without her knowing.

02:40.560 --> 02:43.463
{\an3}- Guys, I am not getting
in one of Lucy's coffins again.

02:43.530 --> 02:45.698
- That won't be necessary.

02:48.868 --> 02:52.772
{\an3}Please keep your arms and legs
inside at all times.

02:52.839 --> 02:55.308
- Aah!

02:55.375 --> 02:56.709
It's all taken care of.

02:56.776 --> 02:59.112
{\an3}Luna will never know
about the concert.

02:59.178 --> 03:00.179
{\an3}- Yo, bro.

03:00.246 --> 03:03.149
I saved you a spot in line!

03:04.484 --> 03:06.252
- Luna, how did you know
about the concert?

03:06.319 --> 03:07.520
- You kidding me?

03:07.587 --> 03:10.356
{\an3}When it comes to music,
I know all.

03:10.423 --> 03:11.691
Are you ready for me to show you

03:11.758 --> 03:14.561
{\an3}how to have the greatest
first concert ever?

03:14.627 --> 03:16.195
- Well, I uh...

03:16.262 --> 03:17.764
- Awesome!

03:17.830 --> 03:21.134
First up, something has to be
done about your duds.

03:22.902 --> 03:25.104
Your threads, man.

03:25.171 --> 03:27.240
Wow, your clothes, dude.

03:27.307 --> 03:28.708
- I think we're fine.

03:28.775 --> 03:31.911
{\an8}<i>[rock guitar riff]</i>

03:31.978 --> 03:33.746
- So much better.

03:33.813 --> 03:36.182
- There's no zipper.
What if I need to pee?

03:36.249 --> 03:38.151
{\an3}- You'll be having too much fun
to pee.

03:38.217 --> 03:41.187
Now let's see your rock pose.

03:42.889 --> 03:44.390
Uh, what's that?

03:44.457 --> 03:47.894
- My rock pose.
I'm igneous.

03:47.961 --> 03:49.295
- No, dudes.

03:49.362 --> 03:53.166
I mean throw up the goats...
like this.

03:53.232 --> 03:54.968
Yeah!

03:55.034 --> 03:56.603
You try.

03:56.669 --> 03:58.071
both: Yeah, uh...

03:58.137 --> 03:59.405
- We'll work on it later.

03:59.472 --> 04:01.107
Now let's see your dance moves.

04:01.174 --> 04:02.342
- I can't dance.

04:02.408 --> 04:05.411
{\an3}- What?
Everybody can dance, man.

04:05.478 --> 04:10.316
{\an3}You just have to feel the music
and move yo booty!

04:10.383 --> 04:12.885
- Whoa!
Ugh!

04:12.952 --> 04:13.987
[gasps]

04:14.053 --> 04:16.956
[shivers and grunts]

04:17.023 --> 04:18.291
- Raspberry or yellow?

04:18.358 --> 04:19.692
- That's it, Lincoln.

04:19.759 --> 04:21.995
Come on, everybody!

04:22.060 --> 04:23.796
Pre-show sing-along.

04:23.863 --> 04:25.465
Sing it with me!

04:25.531 --> 04:27.700
♪ Take my advice
and don't be a mooch ♪

04:27.767 --> 04:30.436
♪ Grab life by the lips
and give it a smooch ♪

04:30.503 --> 04:34.874
Speaking of smooch,
just your type.

04:34.941 --> 04:36.609
Get over here, bro.

04:36.676 --> 04:39.746
There's nothing like falling
in love at your first concert.

04:39.812 --> 04:42.348
all: Oooh!

04:42.415 --> 04:45.284
<i>[dramatic choral music]</i>

04:45.351 --> 04:47.053
- That's it.
We're done here.

04:47.120 --> 04:48.721
{\an3}- Dude,

04:48.788 --> 04:50.289
I'm just trying to make your
first concert unforgettable.

04:50.356 --> 04:51.958
- All you're doing
is embarrassing me.

04:52.025 --> 04:54.060
Our sisters warned me about you.

04:54.127 --> 04:55.461
- What are you talking about?

04:55.528 --> 04:57.163
- They said you ruined
all their first concerts

04:57.230 --> 04:59.332
just like you're
ruining mine now.

04:59.399 --> 05:01.701
- Ouch.
Message received.

05:01.768 --> 05:05.571
If that's the way you feel,
good night, Royal Woods Mall.

05:05.638 --> 05:08.574
Luna Loud has left the building.

05:10.009 --> 05:12.912
- Did I go too far?
Clyde?

05:12.979 --> 05:14.347
Clyde, what are you doing?

05:14.414 --> 05:17.183
{\an1}- My rock pose.
I don't like confrontations.

05:17.250 --> 05:19.352
- Clyde, line's moving.

05:19.419 --> 05:21.020
- Hey, no cuts, kid.

05:21.087 --> 05:22.388
- Back of the line, line-cutter.

05:22.455 --> 05:24.991
- But that was our spot.

05:25.058 --> 05:26.626
Come on.

05:26.693 --> 05:29.629
[clock ticking]

05:32.432 --> 05:33.366
{\an3}We made it!

05:33.433 --> 05:34.567
- Sorry, boys.

05:34.634 --> 05:38.838
{\an8}Smooch is officially sold out.

05:38.905 --> 05:40.573
both: No!

05:40.640 --> 05:43.142
{\an3}- I can't believe we didn't
get Smooch tickets.

05:43.209 --> 05:44.577
- Psst, hey, kid.

05:44.644 --> 05:47.013
{\an1}Did I hear you say
you needed Smooch tickets?

05:47.080 --> 05:48.881
- Yes!
Two, please.

05:51.217 --> 05:52.819
We're in!
- Yes!

05:52.885 --> 05:53.853
[police siren blares]

05:53.920 --> 05:55.021
- You're in, all right.

05:55.088 --> 05:56.355
Incarcerated.

05:56.422 --> 05:57.590
- Are those good seats?

05:57.657 --> 05:59.459
- Buying scalped tickets
is illegal.

05:59.525 --> 06:02.161
Let's go, hooligans.

06:02.228 --> 06:05.098
- Well, might as well
practice my dancing.

06:05.164 --> 06:06.733
- Oh, give it up, kid.

06:06.799 --> 06:09.869
{\an3}My hip can pop and lock
better than you.

06:09.936 --> 06:11.504
- Pipe down, Scoots,

06:11.571 --> 06:14.774
or I'll add disorderly conduct
to your speeding charge.

06:14.841 --> 06:16.242
- I still can't dance, Lincoln.

06:16.309 --> 06:17.543
- What does it matter?

06:17.610 --> 06:19.879
{\an1}We're not going
to the concert anyway.

06:19.946 --> 06:21.013
- Yo, little Loud.

06:21.080 --> 06:22.215
What are you doing here?

06:22.281 --> 06:24.117
- Bobby?
What are you doing here?

06:24.183 --> 06:25.351
- This is my new job.

06:25.418 --> 06:26.786
Lori loves a man in uniform,

06:26.853 --> 06:29.522
plus I'm learning a ton
about police work.

06:29.589 --> 06:30.957
{\an1}Here are those chicken samples
you wanted

06:31.023 --> 06:32.291
from the food court, Captain.

06:32.358 --> 06:34.260
- Great work, Santiago.

06:34.327 --> 06:36.696
{\an3}Now go do a stakeout
at Wok of Art.

06:36.763 --> 06:39.365
{\an3}I think they're giving out
egg rolls.

06:39.432 --> 06:40.366
- Right away, boss.

06:40.433 --> 06:41.901
- [chewing and gulping]

06:41.968 --> 06:44.170
[clock ticking]

06:44.237 --> 06:45.805
Boys, your mom's here.

06:45.872 --> 06:46.873
both: What?

06:46.939 --> 06:49.876
- Oh, my babies!

06:49.942 --> 06:52.044
{\an1}- Luna?
I mean, Mom?

06:52.111 --> 06:55.114
{\an3}- You're lucky I answered the
phone when the fuzz called, bro.

06:55.181 --> 06:57.750
Officer, I'll take it from here.

06:57.817 --> 07:00.186
{\an3}- Yes, ma'am.
Right away, ma'am.

07:00.253 --> 07:01.487
- Your steaks, Captain.

07:01.554 --> 07:02.555
{\an3}- What the heck
are you talking about?

07:02.622 --> 07:04.757
Where are my egg rolls, son?

07:04.824 --> 07:07.960
{\an1}- You said to do a "steak" out,
so--hey, Luna.

07:08.027 --> 07:09.595
- You know their mother?

07:09.662 --> 07:10.863
{\an1}- That's not their mother.
That's his sister.

07:10.930 --> 07:12.165
Nice wig, by the way.

07:12.231 --> 07:13.833
- Wig?
- [giggles]

07:13.900 --> 07:14.934
- Oh, snap.

07:15.001 --> 07:15.935
[cell door closes]

07:16.002 --> 07:17.036
- Sorry, bro.

07:17.103 --> 07:19.539
I fought the law
and the law won.

07:19.605 --> 07:21.274
{\an1}- I can't believe
you came back for us.

07:21.340 --> 07:23.242
- I've been thinking
about what you said,

07:23.309 --> 07:24.777
and you and the girls are right.

07:24.844 --> 07:27.547
{\an3}I do get a little crazy
when it comes to first concerts.

07:27.613 --> 07:29.515
{\an1}- Why are they
so important to you?

07:29.582 --> 07:32.685
- 'Cause my first rock show
changed my life.

07:32.752 --> 07:37.089
<i>It was Mick Swagger,</i>
<i>summer of 7th grade.</i>

07:37.156 --> 07:38.424
<i>The Gimme Swelter Tour.</i>

07:38.491 --> 07:39.992
<i>Up until that muggy June night,</i>

07:40.059 --> 07:42.128
<i>I didn't know</i>
<i>who I wanted to be,</i>

07:42.195 --> 07:44.764
<i>but the moment Mick</i>
<i>and the boys took the stage,</i>

07:44.831 --> 07:48.100
<i>it all started to become clear.</i>

07:48.167 --> 07:50.136
- ♪ It was a hot June night ♪

07:50.203 --> 07:52.471
♪ When she saw the light ♪

07:52.538 --> 07:55.808
♪ Up until then
she didn't know what was right ♪

07:55.875 --> 07:58.077
♪ She showed up at the show ♪

07:58.144 --> 07:59.779
♪ All confused and alone ♪

07:59.846 --> 08:04.483
♪ She had no idea
what was about to unfold ♪

08:04.550 --> 08:06.352
♪ Transformation ♪

08:06.419 --> 08:08.721
<i>- It was like</i>
<i>he was talking to me.</i>

08:08.788 --> 08:12.058
- ♪ A citizen
of the rock and roll nation ♪

08:12.124 --> 08:14.160
♪ Transformation ♪

08:14.227 --> 08:15.962
♪ Total mutation ♪

08:16.028 --> 08:18.998
<i>- It was in that moment</i>
<i>I realized</i>

08:19.065 --> 08:22.201
<i>I was Luna Loud!</i>

08:22.268 --> 08:24.203
Stage dive!

08:24.270 --> 08:26.405
[crowd cheers]

08:26.472 --> 08:28.307
<i>♪</i> ♪

08:28.374 --> 08:30.576
- Wow, I had no idea.

08:30.643 --> 08:32.879
- I know it's only
rock and roll,

08:32.945 --> 08:34.013
but I like it.

08:34.080 --> 08:36.549
{\an3}- [weeping]

08:36.616 --> 08:40.219
I'm sorry, that was just
such a beautiful story.

08:40.285 --> 08:41.419
You're right, kid.

08:41.486 --> 08:44.323
First concerts
are unforgettable.

08:44.390 --> 08:46.525
And I can't let you miss yours.

08:46.592 --> 08:48.427
Here, here's your tickets back.

08:48.494 --> 08:51.230
Now get out of here.

08:51.297 --> 08:54.100
{\an1}- Mall Cop Captain, couldn't
you see it in your heart

08:54.166 --> 08:57.703
{\an1}to let me spend my first concert
with my sister?

08:57.770 --> 08:59.205
A third ticket would mean a lot.

08:59.272 --> 09:03.242
- Well, I just happen
to have this other ticket

09:03.309 --> 09:04.477
here in my pocket,

09:04.543 --> 09:06.345
and since you did
succeed earlier

09:06.412 --> 09:08.814
in pulling at my heartstrings,

09:08.881 --> 09:12.618
I would love for you to attend
the show with your brother.

09:12.685 --> 09:14.520
all: Rock and roll!

09:14.587 --> 09:16.389
{\an1}- You didn't have to do that,
little brother.

09:16.455 --> 09:20.192
{\an3}- I know, but it wouldn't be a
first concert without Luna Loud.

09:20.259 --> 09:22.795
{\an3}I'm sorry I said those things
in the ticket line.

09:22.862 --> 09:24.597
- It's cool, little bro.

09:24.664 --> 09:28.000
{\an1}And don't worry, I promise to be
on my best behave.

09:28.067 --> 09:29.902
- Okay, okay, enough.

09:29.969 --> 09:32.471
{\an1}Now get out of here,
you crazy kids.

09:32.538 --> 09:34.507
[cheering]

09:34.573 --> 09:36.909
Ah, for those about to rock--

09:36.976 --> 09:39.145
- Adios, mall cop!

09:39.211 --> 09:42.114
- Bobby, we got a runner--
I mean a roller.

09:42.181 --> 09:43.316
<i>Cut her off at the food court.</i>

09:43.382 --> 09:45.084
- YOLO!

09:45.151 --> 09:46.652
- Ah, come on.

09:46.719 --> 09:49.555
{\an1}Bobby, you can't just
let a perp--

09:49.622 --> 09:51.424
ooh, is that popcorn shrimp?

09:51.490 --> 09:54.260
<i>♪</i> ♪

09:54.327 --> 09:56.028
- I can't see a thing.

09:56.095 --> 09:58.998
{\an1}Ugh, I thought my first concert
was gonna be unforgettable.

09:59.065 --> 10:02.668
- It could be,
but I don't want to interfere.

10:02.735 --> 10:04.837
- No, please, interfere.

10:04.904 --> 10:08.274
{\an3}- Okay, first up,
we got to get to the front.

10:08.341 --> 10:10.710
- Whoa, I can't cut
in front of all these people.

10:10.776 --> 10:13.245
- That's why they invented
crowd surfing.

10:13.312 --> 10:15.481
both: What?

10:15.548 --> 10:17.783
{\an1}- Whoo!
This is awesome!

10:17.850 --> 10:20.252
- Careful, guys.
Cradle the neck.

10:20.319 --> 10:21.988
- Enjoy the ride, dudes?

10:22.054 --> 10:23.990
- Whoa, how did you
get up here so fast?

10:24.056 --> 10:26.659
{\an3}- I have my ways.
Now come on.

10:26.726 --> 10:28.828
Pose it like you chose it.

10:28.894 --> 10:31.831
- ♪ Smoochy smoochy ♪

10:31.897 --> 10:33.666
♪ Whoo ♪

10:33.733 --> 10:36.235
♪ Whoa whoa ♪

10:36.302 --> 10:37.737
♪ Wet and sloppy ♪

10:37.803 --> 10:39.372
- Boy, did my sisters
have it wrong about Luna.

10:39.438 --> 10:41.073
She's not nuts at all.

10:41.140 --> 10:43.876
She's just really passionate
about the things she loves.

10:43.943 --> 10:45.711
And in the words
of my favorite band,

10:45.778 --> 10:46.846
sometimes you got to...

10:46.912 --> 10:49.248
both: ♪ Grab life by the lips ♪

10:49.315 --> 10:52.151
♪ And give it a smooch ♪

10:52.218 --> 10:54.186
- That's my bro!

10:54.253 --> 10:57.823
- Thanks for making my first
concert unforgettable, Luna!

10:57.890 --> 11:00.793
both: Rock and roll!

11:00.860 --> 11:02.094
- Hold on, hold on, hold on.

11:02.161 --> 11:03.462
This one ended
real great and all,

11:03.529 --> 11:05.731
but I still can't dance,
Lincoln.

11:05.798 --> 11:08.000
- Hold tight, Clyde.

11:08.067 --> 11:11.037
- ♪ Da da smoochity smooch ♪

11:11.103 --> 11:12.238
♪ ♪

11:12.304 --> 11:13.539
- [shivers and grunts]

11:13.606 --> 11:15.608
I'm doing it!
I'm doing it!

11:15.674 --> 11:17.810
- ♪ Give it a smooch ♪

11:22.314 --> 11:25.251
{\an8}<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

11:25.317 --> 11:30.423
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:38.898 --> 11:40.466
- Money.

11:40.533 --> 11:42.868
In the Loud house, there just
isn't a lot of it to go around.

11:46.639 --> 11:48.574
Ew!

11:50.009 --> 11:51.377
Grody!

11:51.444 --> 11:53.112
Which is why,
when you happen to find some,

11:53.179 --> 11:55.915
even the smallest amount,

11:55.981 --> 11:57.983
you've got to keep it
to yourself.

11:58.050 --> 12:00.052
Jackpot!
Mwah!

12:00.119 --> 12:01.187
{\an1}- We heard money.
A dime.

12:01.253 --> 12:02.855
No, a quarter.

12:02.922 --> 12:04.890
- That's impossible.
Money doesn't make a sound.

12:04.957 --> 12:07.860
{\an3}- Haven't you ever heard
the expression "money talks"?

12:07.927 --> 12:09.295
{\an3}[laughs]

12:09.361 --> 12:11.997
- And that quarter is saying,
"Hand me over, bro."

12:12.064 --> 12:13.299
- It's mine!

12:13.365 --> 12:15.367
- Guys, let's just
split it 40/40.

12:15.434 --> 12:17.303
- No, none of you
are getting it.

12:17.369 --> 12:19.305
I found it in the couch
fair and square.

12:19.371 --> 12:20.506
- Wait a second.

12:20.573 --> 12:21.540
If there was one quarter
down there,

12:21.607 --> 12:24.210
then maybe there's more.

12:24.276 --> 12:27.446
[all yelling at once]

12:27.513 --> 12:28.948
- What are they fighting over
this time?

12:29.014 --> 12:30.549
A nickel under the ottoman?

12:30.616 --> 12:32.718
- Nope, a quarter down the sofa.

12:32.785 --> 12:35.688
- We better stop them
before they start biting.

12:35.754 --> 12:36.489
- [chomp]

12:36.555 --> 12:37.690
- Ow!
Lola!

12:37.756 --> 12:38.724
- Too late.

12:38.791 --> 12:40.092
{\an1}[whistles]

12:40.159 --> 12:42.728
{\an1}All right, everybody get
upstairs and clean the attic!

12:42.795 --> 12:45.097
{\an1}That's punishment
for fighting over money.

12:45.164 --> 12:48.234
[all complaining at once]

12:48.300 --> 12:50.536
- That punishment
makes no "cents."

12:50.603 --> 12:51.704
{\an3}[laughs]

12:51.770 --> 12:53.272
- Upstairs.

12:53.339 --> 12:54.940
But that was a good one.

12:55.007 --> 12:58.310
<i>And I want that whole attic</i>
<i>sparkling.</i>

12:58.377 --> 12:59.845
<i>Even the back corner!</i>

12:59.912 --> 13:01.247
[woman screams]

13:01.313 --> 13:04.350
{\an3}- But the back corner
was my secret dark place.

13:04.416 --> 13:07.686
- It's Lincoln's fault we're
up here, so he can do it.

13:07.753 --> 13:10.189
-<i> And watch out</i>
<i>for that loose floorboard!</i>

13:10.256 --> 13:11.790
- What loose floorboard?

13:14.527 --> 13:16.529
Stupid loose floorboard.

13:16.595 --> 13:18.430
Hey, what's this?

13:18.497 --> 13:21.800
"Dear future residents
of 1216 Franklin Avenue,

13:21.867 --> 13:23.402
"my family always
fought over money,

13:23.469 --> 13:25.171
"so I decided to leave
my fortune for you

13:25.237 --> 13:26.639
"in the hope
that you will share it.

13:26.705 --> 13:28.541
"For a clue on where
the money is hidden,

13:28.607 --> 13:30.009
"reflect upon
what I've said here.

13:30.075 --> 13:33.312
Signed, Mrs. Sharon DeMonet,
the original owner."

13:33.379 --> 13:34.914
[gasps]

13:34.980 --> 13:36.182
Hey, guys, check it out.

13:36.248 --> 13:38.184
I found this letter
from the original owner!

13:38.250 --> 13:40.519
She said she's hidden money
in the house.

13:40.586 --> 13:42.621
- Yeah, right, Lincoln.
Quit stalling.

13:42.688 --> 13:45.024
You're not getting out
of cleaning the attic.

13:45.090 --> 13:46.458
all: Yeah!

13:46.525 --> 13:47.993
- Fine, I'll just do it
by myself,

13:48.060 --> 13:50.963
and when I do,
it'll be all mine.

13:54.633 --> 13:56.235
Where'd everybody go?

13:56.302 --> 13:57.536
[metal detector squeaks]

13:57.603 --> 14:00.039
Lisa, what are you doing?

14:00.105 --> 14:03.242
- Um, just calibrating
my dumb human detector.

14:03.309 --> 14:05.077
[detector squeals]

14:05.144 --> 14:08.581
Calibrated.

14:08.647 --> 14:10.482
- Lucy, see anything?

14:10.549 --> 14:11.717
- Lynn, what are you doing?

14:11.784 --> 14:12.718
{\an3}<i>- Aah!</i>

14:12.785 --> 14:13.819
{\an3}<i>[thud]</i>

14:13.886 --> 14:15.087
- Who, me?

14:15.154 --> 14:16.555
No, no, just putting laundry
down the chute.

14:16.622 --> 14:18.657
{\an1}- Laundry doesn't scream
and go thud.

14:18.724 --> 14:20.359
- No, but nosey brothers do.

14:20.426 --> 14:22.528
- Okay, okay!

14:22.595 --> 14:25.064
- Sorry, Luce!
<i>- That's okay.</i>

14:25.130 --> 14:27.833
{\an3}<i>I found a new</i>
<i>secret dark place.</i>

14:31.303 --> 14:33.005
- Looking for something, Lola?

14:33.072 --> 14:34.740
{\an1}- Uh, no.

14:34.807 --> 14:39.578
I'm just practicing for the, uh,
Lil Miss Chimney Sweep Pageant.

14:42.248 --> 14:43.349
- There's nothing up there.

14:43.415 --> 14:44.516
- There's got to be.

14:44.583 --> 14:47.319
Now keep looking!

14:47.386 --> 14:51.090
- Hand me the flashlight.

14:51.156 --> 14:52.324
- Quick, hide!

14:52.391 --> 14:54.460
{\an1}- [grunts]
Okay.

14:54.526 --> 14:55.961
- [whistles]

14:56.028 --> 14:57.062
- What are you up to?

14:57.129 --> 14:59.431
- Just, um, practicing my drums.

14:59.498 --> 15:01.934
[metallic clanging]

15:02.001 --> 15:03.202
[Luan bangs on door]

15:03.269 --> 15:06.438
- Can someone answer
the ringing in my head?

15:06.505 --> 15:08.007
[groans]

15:08.073 --> 15:10.476
<i>- Gross! What is that?</i>
<i>- Get off my pumps!</i>

15:10.542 --> 15:12.878
<i>- I'm gonna pump your face</i>
<i>if you don't move faster.</i>

15:12.945 --> 15:14.813
- Let's just get this over with.

15:14.880 --> 15:18.050
{\an3}- Ugh, why didn't Mrs. DeMonet
just tell us where the money is?

15:18.117 --> 15:20.152
- I don't know.
Let's ask her.

15:20.219 --> 15:21.854
[both scream]

15:21.920 --> 15:23.656
{\an3}- Wait, that's just a leftover
Halloween decoration.

15:23.722 --> 15:25.357
- Hey, what are you two doing?

15:25.424 --> 15:26.992
- Uh, we're just dusting.

15:27.059 --> 15:29.128
{\an1}- Wait, I thought we were
looking for the money.

15:29.194 --> 15:30.596
- I knew it!

15:30.663 --> 15:32.164
Okay, admit it,

15:32.231 --> 15:33.666
{\an1}you're all looking
for the money, aren't you?

15:33.732 --> 15:35.034
- Obviously.
- Uh, duh!

15:35.100 --> 15:36.435
- Heck yes, we are!

15:36.502 --> 15:38.203
- Where'd you find
your first clue, Sherlock?

15:38.270 --> 15:40.406
{\an1}- You guys didn't even
believe the money existed.

15:40.472 --> 15:41.640
I'm the one who should get it.

15:41.707 --> 15:42.741
- Forget that!

15:42.808 --> 15:44.576
I'm finding it for myself.

15:44.643 --> 15:46.512
- Not if I find it first.

15:46.578 --> 15:49.048
- Yeah, dream on.
- It's mine.

15:49.114 --> 15:52.551
[overlapping shouting]

15:52.618 --> 15:54.520
- [whistles]

15:54.586 --> 15:56.422
{\an1}Obviously you haven't learned
your lesson.

15:56.488 --> 15:58.624
Back to the attic.

16:04.563 --> 16:06.332
- The answer must be
in here somewhere.

16:06.398 --> 16:07.633
I know it.

16:07.700 --> 16:09.368
"Reflect upon
what I've said here."

16:09.435 --> 16:11.804
What could that mean?

16:14.640 --> 16:16.775
Reflect!
Duh!

16:19.478 --> 16:22.681
I'm just going to be over here

16:22.748 --> 16:25.551
cleaning the, uh,
the dirty thing.

16:27.653 --> 16:28.587
- What's that?

16:28.654 --> 16:29.655
- Ah!
Nothing.

16:29.722 --> 16:32.424
- Lincoln found another letter.

16:32.491 --> 16:34.493
all: Read it!
[overlapping shouting]

16:34.560 --> 16:36.695
- Okay, okay, calm down.

16:36.762 --> 16:38.297
"Well done.
You've found the next clue.

16:38.364 --> 16:40.699
"But beware, if you fight
like my family did,

16:40.766 --> 16:43.035
you'll never get to
the bottom of the matter."

16:43.102 --> 16:46.372
You guys, maybe we should listen
to her and stop fighting.

16:46.438 --> 16:48.006
- Yeah, Lincoln's right.

16:48.073 --> 16:49.742
{\an1}As soon as we're done
cleaning here,

16:49.808 --> 16:53.712
{\an1}we should totally work together
to find the money.

16:53.779 --> 16:55.781
{\an1}- Hey!
Lori's going after the money!

16:55.848 --> 16:59.184
[all yelling]
- Wait!

16:59.251 --> 17:00.786
<i>[muffled overlapping shouting]</i>

17:00.853 --> 17:04.021
[overlapping shouting]

17:04.089 --> 17:05.190
Guys, the letter.

17:05.257 --> 17:06.724
Remember what Sharon DeMonet
said.

17:06.791 --> 17:07.992
- Forget Sharon DeMonet.

17:08.060 --> 17:10.429
It's every man for himself.

17:10.496 --> 17:12.231
[overlapping shouting]

17:12.297 --> 17:14.333
- Yaaah!
[grunts]

17:14.400 --> 17:15.434
- Smell the money, boy.

17:15.501 --> 17:18.404
Now go find more!

17:18.470 --> 17:19.805
Hey!
Spit it out, Charles!

17:19.872 --> 17:21.839
So help me,
I will get that dollar back,

17:21.906 --> 17:24.643
even if I have to wait for it
to come out the other end!

17:24.710 --> 17:27.746
{\an1}- I summon you
from the great beyond.

17:27.813 --> 17:30.516
Mrs. Sharon DeMonet,

17:30.582 --> 17:33.152
tell me where your fortune is.

17:33.218 --> 17:37.022
Speak to me, oh, spirit.

17:37.089 --> 17:37.956
Come on, lady.

17:38.023 --> 17:40.159
Just tell me where the dough is.

17:40.225 --> 17:41.427
- What did Sharon say?

17:41.493 --> 17:43.328
{\an3}- Sharon said
get out of our room!

17:43.395 --> 17:45.564
- [yelps]

17:47.599 --> 17:49.268
- Hey, look, I found the bread.

17:49.334 --> 17:50.569
[laughs]

17:50.636 --> 17:51.570
And the cheddar.

17:51.637 --> 17:52.771
And the lettuce.

17:52.838 --> 17:54.072
And the clams.

17:54.139 --> 17:55.174
Ew.

17:55.240 --> 17:56.742
No wonder
someone threw this out.

17:56.809 --> 17:58.510
- Hey, what--

17:58.577 --> 18:00.779
{\an3}- Stay out.
This is our turf!

18:00.846 --> 18:03.415
<i>[strums loud rock guitar chord]</i>

18:03.482 --> 18:04.416
[ears ringing]

18:04.483 --> 18:06.285
- Hey, get back here!

18:06.351 --> 18:07.920
That's my dollar!

18:07.986 --> 18:10.756
- Have you found it?
[horn honks]

18:10.823 --> 18:11.924
- Oh, no, you don't!

18:11.990 --> 18:13.625
Search your own room!

18:13.692 --> 18:16.361
- Duh, why didn't I
think of that?

18:20.065 --> 18:21.400
[grunts]

18:21.467 --> 18:22.901
Where are you?

18:22.968 --> 18:25.204
Back, back, you animals!

18:25.270 --> 18:27.372
<i>- I found it!</i>

18:27.439 --> 18:28.841
all: You found the money?

18:28.907 --> 18:31.477
- No, my missing floral pump.

18:31.543 --> 18:32.611
all: Aww.

18:32.678 --> 18:34.446
- The money's not up here.

18:34.513 --> 18:37.249
Maybe it's downstairs.

18:37.316 --> 18:40.252
[overlapping shouting]

18:44.556 --> 18:46.792
[all panting]

18:46.859 --> 18:48.360
- The dining room.

18:48.427 --> 18:51.330
[overlapping shouting]

18:51.396 --> 18:52.931
- The living room!

18:52.998 --> 18:55.701
[overlapping shouting]

18:55.767 --> 18:58.437
- Lily's room!

18:58.504 --> 19:01.640
[all fight silently]

19:03.575 --> 19:06.345
- We've literally searched
the whole house, and nothing.

19:06.411 --> 19:07.412
- Hello?

19:07.479 --> 19:09.681
My floral pump is not nothing.

19:09.748 --> 19:12.384
- Maybe we missed something
in the letter.

19:13.852 --> 19:16.989
[overlapping shouting]

19:18.390 --> 19:19.925
- You're the one who ripped it!
- You did!

19:19.992 --> 19:21.660
{\an3}- Dude, how are we
gonna find the money now?

19:21.727 --> 19:22.828
- We're not.
- Why?

19:22.895 --> 19:24.229
- What are you talking about?

19:24.296 --> 19:25.898
- 'Cause all we did
was fight over it.

19:25.964 --> 19:29.234
And this is exactly what
Sharon DeMonet warned us about.

19:31.837 --> 19:33.205
How about this?

19:33.272 --> 19:35.007
From now on,
any time we find money,

19:35.073 --> 19:37.342
whether it's a hidden fortune
or even this quarter,

19:37.409 --> 19:38.911
we all share it equally.

19:38.977 --> 19:40.746
[overlapping agreements]

19:40.812 --> 19:42.981
- Sounds good.
- Yeah, I kind of like that.

19:43.048 --> 19:45.851
- I'll even share the dollar
I got back from Charles.

19:45.918 --> 19:46.885
- Let's not.

19:46.952 --> 19:48.253
- That thing is dirty money.

19:48.320 --> 19:49.521
{\an3}[Lily coos]

19:49.588 --> 19:51.757
- Aw, we're sorry, Lily.

19:51.823 --> 19:54.359
Did your noisy sisters
and brother wake you?

19:54.426 --> 19:57.062
- Hey, what's that stuck
to Lily's bottom?

19:59.331 --> 20:00.432
- It's a map.

20:00.499 --> 20:02.034
"If you're reading this,

20:02.100 --> 20:05.370
"it means you came together and
got to the bottom of the matter.

20:05.437 --> 20:07.406
Congratulations!
You're almost there."

20:07.472 --> 20:08.840
[all cheer]

20:08.907 --> 20:10.642
But wait, how could she
have known the map

20:10.709 --> 20:13.312
would be on Lily's bottom?

20:13.378 --> 20:16.281
{\an3}- Who cares?
Let's find the money!

20:16.348 --> 20:18.317
[overlapping shouting]

20:19.952 --> 20:21.420
- X marks the spot.

20:21.486 --> 20:24.356
- Ooh, I love solving for X.

20:24.423 --> 20:26.892
all: Dig! Dig! Dig! Dig!

20:26.959 --> 20:29.695
{\an1}- I've got some experience
digging holes.

20:29.761 --> 20:31.330
all: Dig! Dig! Dig! Dig!

20:31.396 --> 20:33.765
- Digging is fun
for the "hole" family.

20:33.832 --> 20:36.401
[laughs]
Get it?

20:36.468 --> 20:38.470
all: Dig! Dig! Dig! Dig!

20:38.537 --> 20:40.706
- Okay, everyone, stand back.

20:40.772 --> 20:42.841
Luna!
A little digging music?

20:42.908 --> 20:44.676
- You got it, sis.

20:44.743 --> 20:45.844
[plays rock music]

20:45.911 --> 20:47.312
- [exhales]

20:47.379 --> 20:49.781
♪ ♪

20:49.848 --> 20:51.984
[all gasp]

20:52.050 --> 20:54.152
- It's locked.
- I got this.

20:56.855 --> 20:58.323
[all gasp]

20:58.390 --> 21:02.294
- What? There's more to my head
than just air, you know.

21:02.361 --> 21:03.562
- [gasps]

21:03.629 --> 21:04.663
[all gasp]

21:04.730 --> 21:08.400
<i>[heavenly choral music]</i>

21:08.467 --> 21:11.737
{\an3}- $500!

21:11.803 --> 21:13.372
[all gasp]

21:13.438 --> 21:15.941
- So if we share it equally,
that means we each get, uh....

21:16.008 --> 21:20.379
- $45.4545455 each.

21:20.445 --> 21:21.713
[cheering]

21:21.780 --> 21:23.048
- Yay. Yay. Yay.
- Yeah, woo-hoo!

21:23.115 --> 21:24.583
- One, two, three!

21:24.650 --> 21:26.518
[overlapping shouting]

21:26.585 --> 21:29.388
- It was really nice of you
to give up your work bonus.

21:29.454 --> 21:31.690
Are you ever gonna tell them
that you're Sharon DeMonet?

21:31.757 --> 21:32.891
{\an1}- Nah.

21:32.958 --> 21:34.660
- I have to admit,

21:34.726 --> 21:36.995
{\an3}it's nice to see them sharing
money and not fighting over it.

21:37.062 --> 21:40.265
{\an3}- Yep.
All part of Sharon's plan.

21:40.332 --> 21:43.035
{\an1}- Was destroying the house
part of Sharon's plan?

21:45.137 --> 21:46.905
- No, no, it was not.

21:46.972 --> 21:50.442
{\an1}- Well, now she can
Sharon DeCleanUp.

21:54.379 --> 21:55.781
- Money.

21:55.847 --> 21:56.882
There just isn't a lot of it
in the Loud house.

21:56.948 --> 21:58.216
But when there is,

21:58.283 --> 21:59.451
it's good to know
that from now on,

21:59.518 --> 22:00.986
the kids will share it.

22:01.053 --> 22:02.320
Ooh, a dime!

22:02.387 --> 22:04.556
I'll just, uh,
keep this one to myself.

22:04.623 --> 22:05.557
[floorboard thuds]

22:10.128 --> 22:11.596
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:11.663 --> 22:13.432
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:13.498 --> 22:16.368
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:16.435 --> 22:18.837
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:18.904 --> 22:22.908
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show</i>
<i>our love in the Loud house ♪</i>

22:22.974 --> 22:24.276
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:24.342 --> 22:25.877
{\an8}<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

22:25.944 --> 22:27.045
{\an8}<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

22:27.112 --> 22:28.280
{\an8}<i>♪ Stand in line to take a pee ♪</i>

22:28.346 --> 22:29.715
{\an8}<i>♪ Never any privacy ♪</i>

22:29.781 --> 22:32.250
{\an8}<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪</i>

22:32.317 --> 22:34.786
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

22:34.853 --> 22:36.154
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
